Package: datadiffr
Title: Compare Data Frames and Render HTML Diff Reports
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Tyler", "Hays", email = "tyhays@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Compare two data frames and visualize the differences as a
    styled, self-contained 'HTML' report. Differences are reported
    cell-by-cell with configurable context rows before and after each
    change, in the style of a unified diff, together with column name and
    type comparison, group-membership comparison, and tolerance-aware
    numeric equality that handles 'NA' and infinite values. Rows are
    matched by position or by key columns. Complements 'waldo' and
    'diffdf', which target console and text output, and provides an
    actively maintained alternative to 'compareDF' and the archived
    'dataCompareR' for report-oriented data comparison workflows.
URL: https://github.com/thays42/datadiffr,
    https://thays42.github.io/datadiffr/
BugReports: https://github.com/thays42/datadiffr/issues
